definition: to utter a high-pitched plaintive or distressed cry
to make a sound similar to such a cry
examples: the wind whined in the chimney

definition: to complain with or as if with a whine
to move or proceed with the sound of a whine
examples: the bullet whined … across the ice

definition: to utter or express with or as if with a whine
a prolonged high-pitched cry usually expressive of distress or pain
a sound resembling such a cry
a complaint uttered with or as if with a whine
